    "# OpenCV"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "OpenCV is an open source Computer Vision Library.\n",
    "\n",
    "OpenCV is an image processing library which deal with images and videos"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Digital images are typically stored in form of Matrix. \n",
    "\n",
    "There are 2 types of Images - a) Coloured Images b) Gray Scaled Images\n",
    "\n",
    "In Gray Scaled Images - we have only 1 channel\n",
    "In coloured Images - we have 3 channels (RGB)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "A grayscale or greyscale image is one in which the value of each pixel is a single sample representing only an amount of light; that is, it carries only intensity information."
   ]
  },
